What you need to know:  Governor Kawira Mwangaza said the event had grown as a brand for the county and the country, and would capitalise on its success to lobby to host the global championshipMwangaza expressed optimism that the race, which is in Athletics Kenya's calendar would attain international recognitionCompetitors will participate in 13km senior men and women races where the winner will pocket Sh500,00, first runners-up Sh300,000 and third place finisher Sh100,000